<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="colour">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Colour.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
The live coloration of this species observed in the recent pair of specimens is a uniform dark purple colour on the dorsal surface of the carapace, ambulatory legs and chelipeds, with a pale purple to dull white on the thoracic sternum, pleon and distal portions of the ambulatory legs and cheliped fingers (Fig. 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="B–F">B-F</normalizedToken>
). The dark purple colouration appears considerably darker when the animal is dry, explaining the original paler colour observation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, PKL" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 12" title="Bornean freshwater crabs of the genus Arachnothelphusa gen. nov. (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Gecarcinucidae)." volume="65" year="1991">Ng (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
